title: Pat Fallon
added: === Attempts to overturn the 2020 United States presidential election ===

On January 6th, 2021, the same day as the [[2021 storming of the United States Capitol]], Fallon, along with 147 of his fellow congressional [[Republican Party (United States)|Republicans]], voted to block certification of the results for Joe Biden's 2020 victory, as part of the [[President trump|Donald Trump]] led effort to [[Attempts to overturn the 2020 United States presidential election|overturn the 2020 United States presidential election]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Yourish |first1=Karen |last2=Buchanan |first2=Larry |last3=Lu |first3=Denise |title=The 147 Republicans Who Voted to Overturn Election Results |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2021/01/07/us/elections/electoral-college-biden-objectors.html |access-date=9 January 2021 |publisher=The New York Times |date=7 January 2021}}</ref>.
